# Modal Pull-Down Dismiss Pattern

All bottom sheet modals must be dismissible by grabbing the drag handle bar at the top and pulling down, **regardless of scroll position**.

## Architecture

The drag handle and ScrollView must be **siblings**, never nested:

```
<Animated.View> {/* modal container with translateY */}
  <View {...panResponder.panHandlers}> {/* drag handle — PanResponder here */}
    <View style={handleBarStyle} />
  </View>
  <ScrollView bounces={true}> {/* scroll content — separate from handle */}
    ...
  </ScrollView>
</Animated.View>
```

## Key Rules

1. **PanResponder goes ONLY on the drag handle View** — never on a parent wrapping the ScrollView (ScrollView's native gestures will always win)
2. **`onStartShouldSetPanResponder: () => true`** — so the handle immediately claims the touch
3. **Dismiss threshold**: pull > 100px OR velocity > 0.4
4. **Visual feedback**: the modal must slide down in real-time as the user drags (`guidePanY.setValue(dy)`)
5. **Snap back**: if not enough pull, spring animate back to 0

## Don't

- Don't put PanResponder on a parent View that also contains a ScrollView
- Don't rely on ScrollView bounce (`contentOffset.y < 0`) for dismiss — user must scroll to top first
- Don't make the handle touch target smaller than ~30pt tall
